physical_appearance: "The image shows a colour transparency. ""Kodachrome Transparency Processed by Kodak"" is stated at the top and inverted at the bottom. An image of a building by a body of water can be seen. It has a two storeys with multiple colonnades. There is a high rise building behind it. The trunk of two trees can be seen in the foreground of the image. "
sgcool_label_text:
This kodachrome colour transparency shows a view of the Fullerton building taken from across the bay, framed by two trees. Inscribed on the verso are ‘Dr Cheah Seng Kee’, ‘99’ and ‘Misty Morning’.   
Kodachrome was a colour film introduced by the Eastman Kodak company in 1935. Its manufacture was discontinued in 2009, and processing ended in 2010.
